-- Shinsei Bank CEO Yashiro Says He Will Resign on Losses, Lack of Dividends
-- Takahiko Hyuga
-- 2010-06-23T01:37:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/shinsei-bank-ceo-yashiro-says-he-will-resign-on-losses-lack-of-dividends.html

          
          
                  June 23 (Bloomberg) -- Masamoto Yashiro , Shinsei Bank
Ltd.’s chief executive officer and president, said he and
several other managing directors will step down to take
responsiblity for the bank’s losses and lack of dividends.
Yashiro spoke today at the company’s annual shareholders
meeting.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Takahiko Hyuga in Tokyo at 
 thyuga@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
